Tale


03 Jun 2017 07:27






The way this one is written seems to be more narrative-driven. I feel like this is clear from the fact that the description doesn't actually state the anomalous effect at all. It lets the reader discover it, but documentation on the SCP would be more straightforward, wouldn't it?

I'd recommend making it drier and more clinical, and then turning the logs into a tale that's linked to it.

It's a great SCP idea, though. I'm just not sure about the method.








There are no metaphors, only half-truths and good intentions.






