I agree with what Corinth had to say here, you have one of the anomalous effects being revealed through the narrative of the addendums. You've got a really good case of showing instead of telling, which is usually a good thing. But in this case the thing you're showing is something that should be told. Tell us the anomalous effects, then show us the extent of that effect or why the effect is scary/creepy/worth containing.

I really like the concept, the only thing keeping me from voting is what I stated above. Neutral vote for now.







